08/04/2010
TREBINJE, Bosnia and Herzegovina -- Police seized 155kg of marijuana on Wednesday (April 7th) in the municipality of Trebinje. The stash, worth 600,000 euros, was found in a truck. The two drivers were arrested. Meanwhile, police searched seven locations in several cities across the country, and five other arrests were made. The raids were part of an ongoing investigation being carried out in collaboration with police and judicial authorities in Montenegro, Serbia and Slovenia. (RTRS, Srna, Dnevni Avaz, AP - 07/04/10)
